udicious, and accessible study sheds new light on the roots of the contemporary doctrine of humanitarian intervention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aHumanitarian interventionzFormer Yugoslav Republics. 0aYugoslav War, 1991-1995. 4aConflict and Peace. 4aHistory. 4aPLS. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 7aHISTORY / Military / General.2bisacsh  aHumanitaire interventie.  aR2P.  aSrebenica.  aVoormalig Joegoslavië.  aetnisch conflict.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311070067108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060651508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102378608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z97831106627880 cprintz978908964563040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048519675?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048519675423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048519675/original  a978-3-11-060651-5  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066278-8  Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2002d2015  a978-3-11-070067-1  AUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-102378-6  Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK